docs.description:
The BetterInvesting 100 Index is an equal-weighted index that is designed to track the performance of the 100 securities held by the largest number of the National Association of Investors Corporation ("NAIC") member clubs, based on an annual survey of its members.On April 9, 2007, the BetterInvesting 100 Index began with a base value of 150.00. * NASDAQ is calculating this index as a service provider to NAIC and is not involved in determining the index membership.

Components: 101

Currency: USD

Entitlements: U.S. Classic (NASDAQ / PHLX)

Total Market Value: is the sum of the market value of all companies in the index.

Dividend Market Value: is the sum of the market value of all dividends generated by companies in the index.

Terms of Use: This data cannot be republished or used as the basis of a financial product without the permission of Nasdaq OMX.

docs.description: OMO Repo Transaction Details provides a summary of the type of securities delivered to/by the RBA under (Reverse) Repo at each term dealt through the Open Market Operations.  'Term' is the number of days dealt in open market operations.  'Value Dealt' is the amount of the first leg of securities bought/sold by the RBA under (Reverse) Repo.  Withdrawal of funds (Repo transactions) from the aggregate Exchange Settlement (ES) Account pool of funds is shown as a negative (-) figure.  Injection (Reverse Repo) of funds into the aggregate ES Account pool of funds is shown as a positive (+) figure.  ‘Weighted average rate' is the is the average of the rates on (Reverse) Repos dealt by the Bank through Open Market Operations, weighted by the amount transacted.
docs.name: Reserve Bank Of Australia Open Market Operations - Repo Transaction Details

docs.description:
Official Zacks consensus Annual earnings estimates for Fuel Tech Inc. (FTEK) expressed in earnings per share (EPS). This is an estimate of EPS in USD before non-recurring items and including employee stock options expenses. For complete details about Zacks' estimation methodology, see the Documentation tab on the Zacks Earnings Estimates database home page.

Currency: USD

Column Definitions

The DATE column corresponds to the last day of the reporting period to which the estimate applies, not the actual reporting date. Use FISC_YEAR, FISC_QTR, CAL_YEAR, CAL_QTR for mapping the estimate to a fiscal or calendar year and quarter.

EPS_MEAN_EST: The arithmetic mean of all EPS estimates.

EPS_MEDIAN_EST: The median of all EPS estimates.

EPS_HIGH_EST: The highest EPS estimate.

EPS_LOW_EST: The lowest EPS estimate.

EPS_CNT_EST: The number of reporting analysts for this company and the denominator for the calculation of EPS_MEAN_EST.

EPS_STD_EST: The standard deviation of all EPS estimates.

EPS_PCT_CHG_EST: The percent difference between EPS_MEAN_EST and the actual EPS reported for the same quarter 12 months prior. Hence this field is the consensus earnings growth estimate for the last 12 months. Note this should not be mistaken for a long term growth estimate.

FISC_YEAR: The fiscal year to which this estimate applies.

FISC_QTR: The fiscal quarter to which this estimate applies.

CAL_YEAR: The calendar year to which this estimate applies.

CAL_QTR: The calendar quarter to which this estimate applies.

PER_CODE: The fiscal period reference in relation to the most recently reported period. The most recently reported period is designated as 0. The next period is designated 1. The period after that is 2. Etc. The fiscal period designations roll on each earnings report date, not on calendar period end dates.

Technical Notes: FISC_YEAR, FISC_QTR, CAL_YEAR, CAL_QTR, PER_CODE should be treated as integers, even though the Quandl API will send them as floats.

Premium Support is available for subscribers of this dataset: premium_support@quandl.com
docs.name: Fuel Tech Inc. (FTEK) Current Annual Earnings (EPS) Estimates

docs.description:
Underlying Futures Contract: CBOT Dow Jones Ind Avg (DJIA) (DJ)

Depth: Continuous Futures Contract #1 (DJ1)

Roll Date:Roll on Last Trading Day. Contracts roll on the last trading day of the expiring or front contract. Thus the continuous contract history is a non-overlapping end-to-end concatenation of underlying individual contracts, spliced on successive expiry dates.

Price Adjustment:Forwards Panama Canal Method. Price histories of each underlying contract are shifted up or down by a constant amount, starting with the oldest contract and working forwards, so as to eliminate jumps in price between consecutive contracts. Note that in this method, the current continuous contract price does not match the current underlying futures price, due to the cumulative effect of all the historical adjustments.

Methodology: To read more about the Stevens roll date and price adjustment methodology, see the Documentation tab on the Stevens Continuous Futures database home page.

Contract Size:$10 x Dow Jones Industrial Average (DJIA)

Deliverable Good:None, this contract is cash settled.

Tick Size:1.00 index points=$10.00

Pricing Unit:Index Points

Columns: Open, High, Low, Settle, Volume, Previous Day Open Interest. Note that Open Interest is always reported for the previous trading day, to avoid lookahead bias.
docs.name: CBOT Dow Jones Ind Avg (DJIA) Futures #1 (DJ1) - Forwards Panama Adjusted Prices, Roll On Last Trading Day, Continuous Contract History
